Chelsea agreed to sign defender
Wallace Oliveira dos Santos from Brazilian club Fluminense
during the January transfer period.  As part of the agreement, the 18-year-old will remain with
Fluminense until the end of the season, Chelsea said on its
website.  The 18-year-old made his senior debut in  Brazil  this season
and made 18 appearances in helping Fluminense to the league
championship and the Rio State League and the Guanabara Cup
titles.  An under-20 international, he was part of the Brazil team
that last year won the South American under-17 championship and
finished fourth at the World Cup in  Mexico .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  